description:
Easy Piano Tutorial Exercises by Oscar Peterson! Exercise 8 of 14
Whether you are interested in learning Jazz piano, or piano in general, these beginner jazz piano exercises are very fun, enjoyable and helpful to learn and play for everyone, both adult and youngster alike. Written by the late great Jazz pianist Oscar Peterson, these exercises aim to help condition the hands for proceeding into deeper jazz and piano playing. Oscar Peterson recommended that it is vitally important that all fingering given in both hands be followed completely. In the exercises where no fingering is given, Oscar felt that the player should instinctively have no trouble finding the proper digital position to give the greatest ease of hand movement, thereby achieving a better tonal result on the piano. 

Now for the first time, you can learn, practice and play-along with our piano tutorial video; making daily practice fun and interesting. Notice that the notes have a "swing feel" to them in our video, and this will help you create a feeling for the Jazz swing sound. And because the music is at a nice tempo for practice and is nice and steady, you won't need a metronome - just play-along with the video each day!

I hope you have lots of fun with these 14 exercises originally written by Oscar Peterson, and updated by me. I have also managed to spot errors in the original music, and I have corrected these errors, so you have wonderfully accurate music, in a fun learning format. If you practice this exercises with my videos daily, you will find your piano playing improving, as well as your sense of timing, harmony and melody. These exercises are also great for warming up the muscles in your arms, hands and fingers. As you progress with these exercises, you can start practicing at faster tempos, and in all keys - a great challenge for even the most advanced piano players! 

You might also enjoy my video entitled: PIANO MASTERCLASS - Oscar Peterson Demonstrates Jazz Piano Styles! Piano Tutorial Remastered. https://youtu.be/QqPhypQAhU8 This is an edited interview with Oscar Peterson. I have remastered the video and audio of the old footage, so you can hear Oscar's wisdom and piano playing in high quality stereo sound. Oscar demonstrates various Jazz piano styles, and the video closes with Oscar playing an improvisation which demonstrates his own style and playing.
